German States’ Budget Deficits Decline, Handelsblatt Reports

-- B y   H o l g e r   E l f e s
-- 
2011-06-29T17:04:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/german-states-budget-deficits-decline-handelsblatt-reports.html
Germany ’s states have reduced their
budget deficits in the first five months of the year,
 Handelsblatt  reported today, citing calculations by the federal
 Finance Ministry .  The shortfalls amounted to 6.3 billion euros ($9.1
billion), 4.8 billion euros less than a year earlier, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Holger Elfes in Dusseldorf at 
 helfes@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 